Instructions for registering client systems you wish to manage with Spacewalk

= Before Starting =
  1. Create a base channel within Spacewalk (Channels > Manage Software Channels > Create New Channel)
  1. Create an activation key with the new base channel.



= Fedora 9 =

  1. Install the Spacewalk yum repository by creating a file in /etc/yum.repos.d with the following contents:
    {{{
[spacewalk]
name=Spacewalk
baseurl=http://spacewalk.redhat.com/yum/fedora/9/i386/
gpgkey=http://www.redhat.com/spacewalk/yum/RPM-GPG-KEY-spacewalk
enabled=1
gpgcheck=1
}}}
  1. Install client packages:
    {{{
yum install rhn-client-tools rhn-check rhn-setup rhnsd m2crypto yum-rhn-plugin
    }}}
  1. Register your Fedora system to Spacewalk using the activation key you created earlier.
{{{
  rhnreg_ks --force --serverUrl=http://YOURSATELLITEURL/XMLRPC --activationkey=<key-with-fedora-custom-channel> 
}}}

= CentOS 5 =

  1. Install required packages before the red hat network packages: 
    {{{
yum -q -y install usermode-gtk pyOpenSSL 1>/dev/null 2>&1
    }}}
  2. Download and Install client packages:
    {{{
wget 'link-to website'
rpm -Uvh *.rpm
    }}}
  3. Register your CentOS system to Spacewalk using the activation key you created earlier.
{{{
  rhnreg_ks --force --serverUrl=http://YOURSATELLITEURL/XMLRPC --activationkey=<key-with-fedora-custom-channel> 
}}}

